Gulf Stocks: Dubai’s Emaar Properties and Saudi Basic Industries

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-05-16T13:40:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/gulf-stocks-dubai-s-emaar-properties-and-saudi-basic-industries.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  slumped 1.4
percent and Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  dropped 0.5 percent at
the 2 p.m. close.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Emaar Properties PJSC (EMAAR)  , builder of the world’s
tallest skyscraper, retreated to the lowest since March 23,
losing 2.2 percent to 3.1 dirhams. Dubai Bank PJSC, an Islamic
lender owned by Dubai Holding LLC and Emaar, was rescued by the
Dubai government after loan losses mounted as the emirate
grappled with a debt crisis.  Saudi Basic Industries Corp. (SABIC AB), the region’s
biggest petrochemicals maker, declined 0.9 percent to 106.5
riyals, the lowest level since April 18. Oil for June delivery
fell as much as 2 percent to $97.67 a barrel on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
